<subSubSection pageId="108" pageNumber="109" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="108.[151,1436,725,1002]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,833,858]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Notes.</emphasis>
Several biological notes on this ground-nesting species are available (
<bibRefCitation author="Hurd" box="[1108,1240,833,858]" firstAuthor="Hurd" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" pagination="1741 - 2209" refId="ref90811" refString="Hurd, P. D. (1979) Superfamily Apoidea. In: Krombein, K. V., Hurd Jr., P. D., Smith, D. R. &amp; Burks, B. D. (Eds.), Catalog of Hymenoptera in America North of Mexico. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D. C., pp. 1741 - 2209." type="book chapter" year="1979">Hurd 1979</bibRefCitation>
), including from Missouri (
<bibRefCitation author="Rau" box="[266,380,870,894]" firstAuthor="Rau" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" pagination="1 - 71" refId="ref99590" refString="Rau, P. (1922) Ecological and behavior notes on Missouri insects. Transactions of the Academy of Science of St. Louis, 24, 1 - 71." type="journal article" year="1922">Rau 1922</bibRefCitation>
), Colorado (
<bibRefCitation author="Hicks" box="[520,655,869,894]" firstAuthor="Hicks" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" pagination="217 - 252" refId="ref90254" refString="Hicks, C. H. (1926) Nesting habits and parasites of certain bees of Boulder County, Colorado. The University of Colorado Studies, 26, 217 - 252." type="journal article" year="1926">Hicks 1926</bibRefCitation>
), New York (
<bibRefCitation author="Eickwort" box="[806,1041,869,894]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Eickwort" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" pagination="557 - 570" refId="ref87460" refString="Eickwort, G. C., Matthews, R. W. &amp; Carpenter, J. (1981) Observations on the nesting behavior of Megachile rubi and M. texana with a discussion of the significance of soil nesting in the evolution of megachilid bees (Hymenoptera: Megachilidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 54, 557 - 570." type="journal article" year="1981">
Eickwort 
<emphasis box="[918,975,869,894]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">et al.</emphasis>
1981
</bibRefCitation>
), North Carolina (
<bibRefCitation author="Krombein" box="[1247,1428,869,894]" firstAuthor="Krombein" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" pagination="84 - 85" refId="ref92021" refString="Krombein, K. V. (1953) A note on the nesting habits of Megachile texana Cresson (Hymenoptera, Megachilidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 55, 84 - 85." type="journal article" year="1953">Krombein 1953</bibRefCitation>
) and Florida (
<bibRefCitation author="Krombein" box="[295,478,905,930]" firstAuthor="Krombein" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" pagination="415" refId="ref92128" refString="Krombein, K. V. (1970) Another note on the nesting habits of Megachile texana Cresson (Hymenoptera: Megachilidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 72, 415." type="journal article" year="1970">Krombein 1970</bibRefCitation>
). Shallow nests, a few inches long, were also observed in flat sandy soil in Michigan (
<bibRefCitation author="Gibbs" box="[158,295,941,966]" firstAuthor="Gibbs" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" pagination="17 - 24" refId="ref88558" refString="Gibbs, J. (2017) Notes on the nests of Augochloropsis metallica fulgida and Megachile mucida in central Michigan (Hymenoptera: Halictidae, Megachilidae). The Great Lakes Entomologist, 50, 17 - 24." type="journal article" year="2017">Gibbs 2017</bibRefCitation>
). One was adjacent to a highbush blueberry field in Van Buren County and a second was in a clearing at Rose Lake, Shiawassee County.
</paragraph>
